text: The H.G. Newman Building is a historic commercial building located in downtown Evansville, Indiana. It was built in 1900, and is a two-story, Late Victorian style brick building. The building features decorative brickwork and parapet, and round arched openings. It was originally built to house a wholesale grocery and farmers' supply.
